    <content type='html'>evidently there has been some controversy as to the meaning of our band name: 

&lt;a href="http://www.christianpornmachine.com"&gt;christian porn machine&lt;/a&gt;

note that it's not:
"&lt;i&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.thesmashingpumpkins.com"&gt;the&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/i&gt;" christian porn machine

that would be presumptious.

it's just christian porn machine.  say it a few times and you'll like the ring of it.  right away you say to yourself:  "what the hell are they thinking"

good question.  let me (try to) explain (not very well)

&lt;a href="http://www.gravattville.com/mf/foucault.html"&gt;foucault &lt;/a&gt;said: "&lt;i&gt;there is a difference between art and propaganda and in fact there is no difference between propaganda and pornography&lt;/i&gt;"

he then went on to explain:
&lt;blockquote&gt;
"&lt;i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;art is to promote reflection on deep seeded emotion

"&lt;i&gt;propaganda and pornography are used to simply get immediate reaction and promote gratification or action. They do not promote thought but rather inhibit it by getting the observer to ignore what he or she actually thinks/believes and act in accordance with the propagandist or pornographer.&lt;/i&gt;"
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;img src="http://www.gravattville.com/blogpictures/mf.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
get it?  read it several times, i know it's hard, but just keep telling yourself that you are getting a college level education in 
&lt;a href="http://publishing.cambridge.org/hss/philosophy/"&gt;french philosophy&lt;/a&gt;.  read it again, i'll wait ....

ok now listen.  speaking for myself, i am slightly critical of the evangelical christian &lt;a href="http://www.gracechurch.org/"&gt;church&lt;/a&gt;.

i love christ.

although i've not said that publicly in well over a year

i hate what his church has become.  everything he ever said about what his *gathering* was supposed to be like has been so utterly corrupted that it has become disgusting and that's speaking for myself mind you.  imagine what he would say.  it's my belief that if he returned today he would unequivocally denounce what christianity has become. in foucault's words, christ would tell us that the gospel has become porn. it is used to simply get and promote action. what the gospel is now does not promote thought but rather inhibits it by getting the soul to ignore what he or she actually thinks/believes and act in accordance with the pornographer (evangelist) no one is treating the gospel/christianity like it was intended to be treated:  to promote reflection on deep seeded emotion.

the church has become one giant 
*&lt;a href="http://www.christianpornmachine.com"&gt;christian porn machine&lt;/a&gt;*.

our band is about art.  
we do what your churches try to do and fail.
we can replace your church.
</content>
