    <content type='html'>&lt;br&gt;
&lt;b&gt;there seems to be some confusion about our &lt;a href="http://www.christianpornmachine.com"&gt;band name&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (part2)
&lt;br&gt;
the best thing about having a wife that is a graduate student is that you get to skip to all of the soft-porn sections of famous literature.  just kidding.  but you do get a secondary education as you follow her reading assignments.
&lt;br&gt;
the following excerpt is from charles dickens:  the pickwick papers.  it is the story of a few men who travel the globe in search of fun times, learning and adventures.  along the way dickens, uses every possible means to debunk the popular form of christianity. evidently charlie knew in advance when he wote this classic that his humor may not be appreciated by the local faith-practicers.  so he included this preface.  read it slowly and sever times if necesssary.  it is appropriate for today.
&lt;br&gt;
then read my comments at the bottom (please)
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;img src="http://www.gravattville.com/blogpictures/pickwicktop.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;i&gt;lest there be any well-intentioned persons who do not perceive the difference between religion and the cant of religion, piety and the pretence of piety, a humble reverence for the great truths of scripture and an audacious and offensive obtrusion of it's letter and not it's spirit in the commonest dissensions and meanest affairs of life, to the extraordinary confusion of ignorant minds, let them understand that it is always the latter, and never the former, which is satirized here.  &lt;/i&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;i&gt;further, that the latter is satirized as being, according to all experience, inconsistent with the former, impossible of union with it, and one of the most evil and mischievous falsehoods existent in society - whether it establish it's head-quarters, for the time being in exeter hall, or ebezener chapel, or both.  it may appear unnecessary to offer a word of observation on so plain a head.  but it is never out of season to protest against that coarse familiarity with sacred things which is busy on the lip, and idle in the heart;  or against the confounding of christianity with any class of persons who, in the words of swift, have just enough religion to make them hate, and not enough to make them love one another.&lt;/i&gt;
&lt;img src="http://www.gravattville.com/blogpictures/pickwickbottom.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
one of the points here is that satire is and has been one of the greatest teachers.  if you say something nice, few people hear you, but if you say something offensive, everyone seems to take notice.  satire &lt;i&gt;can &lt;/i&gt;be described as saying something true and nice, in very offensive and disturbing way, so as to call attention to the point.
&lt;br&gt;
like most art it is often misunderstood.  but like most good art, it is also effective in communicating.
&lt;br&gt;
when you hear the words christian and porn together, at least it makes you mad.  that's better than not noticing .  at least now we've got your attention and we can re-direct it wherever we want.
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;br&gt;</content>
